      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: My bridegroom-king has a vineyard of lovemade from a multitude of
        followers. [[COMMENT(0)]]His caretakers of this vineyardhave given my beloved
        their best.
      comments:
      - number: 8:11
        content: "  The Hebrew text literally means \u201CSolomon had a vineyard
          at Baal-hamon.\u201D The king\u2019s vineyard is a picture of the church,
          the called-out multitude of those who follow Jesus (;  ). Baal-hamon can
          be translated \u201Clord of a multitude,\u201D \u201Clord of an uproar,\u201D
          or \u201Clord of wealth.\u201D    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: But as for my own vineyard of love,I give all the glory to you. [[COMMENT(0)]]And
        I will give double honor to those who serve my belovedand have watched over
        my soul.
      comments:
      - number: 8:12
        content: "  Or \u201Cyou may have the thousand (shekels), O&nbsp;Solomon.\u201D
          The number one thousand is a biblical symbol for the glory of God. The
          prize of mature sonship is a truth that defies description, and all the
          glory of the vineyard belongs to our King, one greater than Solomon.     
          Or \u201Cthe two hundred.\u201D This is two times one hundred. The number
          one hundred represents the children of the promise. Abraham was one hundred
          when Isaac, the promised seed, was born (). Isaac was a type of the children
          of promise, the spiritual seed (;  ). The number one hundred is also connected
          to Isaac\u2019s sowing and reaping, and the blessing of God (). The Lord
          will receive the hundred-fold fruit of his life in us (). Jesus has one
          hundred sheep in his fold (). The number two is the symbol of witness.
          Two hundred reveals the witness of God\u2019s sons coming forth ().  "
